title.value: Cross-version ValueSet R5.CombinedDoseForm for use in FHIR R4

description.value: This cross-version ValueSet represents content from `http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/combined-dose-form|5.0.0` for use in FHIR R4.

purpose.value:
This value set is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the value set `http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/combined-dose-form|5.0.0` as defined in FHIR R5 in FHIR R4.
The source value set is bound to the following FHIR R5 elements: * `MedicinalProductDefinition.combinedPharmaceuticalDoseForm` as Example
Across FHIR versions, the value set has been mapped as: * `http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/combined-dose-form|5.0.0` * `http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/combined-dose-form|4.3.0`
The following concepts are not included in this cross-version definition because they have valid representations * _no concepts_
Following are the generation technical comments: All concepts in the comparison are listed as identical. The source and target value sets have the same number of active concepts (77).
